[32m+[m[32m# 📊 SDLC — Waterfall Methodology[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> **A linear, sequential approach to software development — each phase must fully complete before the next one begins. No going back!**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m![SDLC Waterfall Methodology](./assets/sdlc-waterfall.svg)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 📌 What is Waterfall?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe **Waterfall model** is one of the earliest and most straightforward Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodologies. It follows a strict top-down approach where progress flows in one direction — like a waterfall — through clearly defined phases.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🔄 Stages Flow: One Step at a Time[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 1. 🗂️ Planning[m
[32m+[m[32m**What are we building?**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Define project scope & goals[m
[32m+[m[32m- Estimate time & budget[m
[32m+[m[32m- Assign team roles & responsibilities[m
[32m+[m[32m- Feasibility analysis[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2. 📋 Requirements[m
[32m+[m[32m**What features are needed?**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Gather all user & business needs[m
[32m+[m[32m- Produce a **Software Requirements Specification (SRS)** document[m
[32m+[m[32m- Identify Functional & Non-functional requirements[m
[32m+[m[32m- Get formal sign-off from the client[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 3. 🏗️ System Design[m
[32m+[m[32m**How will we build it?**[m
[32m+[m[32m- High-Level Design (HLD) & Low-Level Design (LLD)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Database schema & API design[m
[32m+[m[32m- UI/UX wireframes[m
[32m+[m[32m- Tech stack decisions[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 4. 💻 Implementation (Coding)[m
[32m+[m[32m**Actually writing the code!**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Developers write code strictly following design documents[m
[32m+[m[32m- Unit testing done by developers[m
[32m+[m[32m- Code reviews & commits[m
[32m+[m[32m- No scope changes allowed at this stage[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 5. 🧪 Testing & QA[m
[32m+[m[32m**Does it work correctly?**[m
[32m+[m[32m- QA team tests all features[m
[32m+[m[32m- Types: Unit → Integration → System → UAT[m
[32m+[m[32m- Bug fix cycles[m
[32m+[m[32m- User Acceptance Testing (UAT) with real users[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 6. 🚀 Deployment[m
[32m+[m[32m**Go Live to Production!**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Release to production server[m
[32m+[m[32m- User training & documentation[m
[32m+[m[32m- Rollback plan kept ready[m
[32m+[m[32m- Handover to operations team[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 7. 🔧 Maintenance[m
[32m+[m[32m**Keep it running smoothly!**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Bug fixes post-release[m
[32m+[m[32m- Performance tuning[m
[32m+[m[32m- Security patches & updates[m
[32m+[m[32m- Feature enhancement requests[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🏠 Real World Analogy: Building a House[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mLay blueprint  →  Get permits (requirements)  →  Architect draws design[m
[32m+[m[32m      →  Builders construct  →  Inspector checks  →  Family moves in  →  Annual maintenance[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mJust like constructing a house — you can't pour the foundation before the blueprint is approved, and you can't move in before the inspector signs off.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## ✅ Pros of Waterfall[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Advantage | Details |[m
[32m+[m[32m|-----------|---------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| 📐 Clear Structure | Easy to understand and follow for all team members |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 📄 Well Documented | Every stage produces thorough documentation |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 🎯 Fixed Scope | Works great when all requirements are known upfront |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 📅 Easy Milestones | Simple to track progress and deadlines |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 👥 Client Clarity | Client knows exactly what to expect and when |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## ❌ Cons of Waterfall[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Disadvantage | Details |[m
[32m+[m[32m|--------------|---------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| 🔒 Inflexible | Difficult to accommodate changing requirements |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 🐛 Late Testing | Bugs are discovered only near the end |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 👁️ No Early Demo | Client sees working software only at the finish line |[m
[32m+[m[32m| ⚠️ High Risk | Misunderstood requirements cause costly rework |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 🔄 No Iteration | No feedback loops between phases |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🏆 Best Use Cases[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWaterfall works best when you can answer **YES** to all 3 questions:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Are requirements **fully known** upfront?[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Will the scope **NOT change** mid-project?[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Is **heavy documentation** required?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Industries where Waterfall shines:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Industry | Examples |[m
[32m+[m[32m|----------|---------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| 🏛️ Government Systems | Tax portals, public records, defence software |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 🏦 Banking & Finance | Core banking, loan processing, payment gateways |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 🏥 Healthcare & Medical | Hospital mgmt, patient records, medical devices |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 🏗️ Construction & Engineering | CAD/CAM tools, infrastructure management |[m
[32m+[m[32m| ✈️ Aerospace & Defence | Flight controls, satellite software, navigation |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## ⚖️ Waterfall vs Agile — Quick Comparison[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Factor | Waterfall | Agile |[m
[32m+[m[32m|--------|-----------|-------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Approach | Linear & Sequential | Iterative & Incremental |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Flexibility | Low — fixed scope | High — welcomes change |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Client Involvement | Beginning & end only | Continuous collaboration |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Delivery | Single final delivery | Frequent small releases |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Documentation | Heavy & detailed | Light & just-in-time |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Best For | Stable, well-defined projects | Dynamic, evolving projects |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Risk | Higher (late feedback) | Lower (early feedback) |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
